## Creating and Maintaining Product Vision

### Hierarchy

| Company Level | Product Level |
|---------------|----------------|
| Mission, Vision, Values | Product Vision |
| Objectives & Key Results | How value will be created |
| Themes | Problems to solve |
| Features & Solutions | What will be built |

### A Good Product Vision

- States the main goal of the product
- Clarifies the problem being solved
- Defines value delivered to users

---

## Product Vision Board Components

| Element | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **Target Group** | Who are the primary users (e.g., students, professionals) |
| **Pain Points** | e.g., boring online learning, lack of feedback |
| **Product Value** | How the product solves the pain |
| **Key Features** | e.g., personalized feedback, AI-based course recommendations |
| **Business Goals & KPIs** | e.g., 20% premium signups, $10M revenue in 3 years |
| **Market Trends** | e.g., EdTech growing at 16% CAGR to 2030 |
| **Competitors** | e.g., Coursera, Udemy |
| **Competitive Advantage** | e.g., AI personalization, real-time engagement |
| **Revenue Streams** | Pay-per-course, B2B partnerships |
| **Cost Factors** | Dev cost, outsourcing, marketing |

---

## Differentiation and Competitive Analysis

### Why Do Competitive Research?

- Identify standard features and best practices
- Learn how others solve problems
- Discover innovation opportunities
- Uncover unmet customer needs
- Avoid reinventing the wheel

### Types of Competitors

1. **Direct** – Offer same product to same customers
2. **Indirect** – Substitutes or similar offerings
3. **Complementary** – Products that enhance yours

---

## Where to Find Competitive Data

1. **Online research** – Sites, blogs, reviews
2. **Use competitor’s product**
3. **Talk to users**
4. **Attend trade shows and conferences**

---

## Comparison Matrix

| Feature | Your Product | Competitor A | Competitor B |
|--------|--------------|--------------|--------------|
| Feature 1 | ✓ | ✓ | ✗ |
| Feature 2 | ✗ | ✓ | ✓ |
| UX | Excellent | Good | Poor |

